 #overflow properties
 - visible: the overflow is not clipped. it renders outside the element's box. this is default. 
   overflow:visible
- hidden: the overflow is clipped, and the rest of the content will n=be invisible. content cna be scrolled programmatically (eg by setting scrollLeft to scrollTo())
  overflow:hidden;
- clip:the overflow is clipped,and the rest of the content will be invisible.forbirds scrolling, inlcuding programmatic scrolling.
  overflow:clip;
- scroll: the overflow is clipped, but a scroll-bar is added to see the rest of the content 
  overflow:scroll;
- auto:if the overflow is clipped, a scroll-bar should be added to see the rest of the content.
  overflow:auto;
- initial:sets this property to its default value. read about initial 
  overflow:initial;
- inherit:inherits this property form its parent element. read about inherit
  overflow:inherit;
